commit_message:
Navigation + cleanup for details pages

Adds a common detail page and a breadcrumb templatetag. The breadcrumb
templatetag defaults to displaying the panel name and the existing page
title, which is usually name_or_id. The templatetag can also access the
context, and accepts a "custom_breadcrumb", for complex nested pages or
customised layouts.

This type of navigation is also useful for small devices (mobile/
tablet), providing logical direction that isn't dependant on the
sidebar being displayed.

Currently implemented in Images, Volumes (simple breadcrumb), Ports and
Subnets (more complex nesting).

This approach has been chosen as manipulation of the URLs was seen as
undesirable, making request.path too unreliable. Furthermore, the
templatetag seperation means this could easily be used in other views.

NOTE: The network details page itself will be updated following the
resolution of https://bugs.launchpad.net/horizon/+bug/1416838

Change-Id: I7443b2ffa61560e5d1fd4d6d91b11201f1db6fac

commit_message:
Define non_admin_status_resources in each test

Previously non_admin_status_resources for each resource
is defined in the common test module test_cli20.py.
This means when we add a new resoruce without admin_status_up
we need to change the common test module.
This commit moves non_admin_status_resources into each test.

Change-Id: Ieefa87eedcbabf083c127df893c11ad265f590b1

commit_message:
Replace oslo_utils.timeutils.isotime

'oslo_utils.timeutils.isotime()' is deprecated in version '1.6' and
will be removed in a future version: use datet ime.datetime.isoformat()
instead.

Change-Id: Ie1460d7a8b9b3f3b9f982725435d963a561a3fab
Closes-Bug: #1514331

commit_message:
Fix server.action does not work

As description in nova api document, server action request should use
the post method, with no response body return.

Fix this bug by modified request method from 'put' to 'post', and
also add a boolean parameter 'has_response' in action method to avoid
empty response body exception in response parsing.

Change-Id: Ie37e9745b3c924049f7fd563e43e5de55c711af7
Closes-Bug:#1509141

commit_message:
Removing incongruent section from 'Why and How' section

The 'Why and How' section of this is about the creation of the
document, so removing the one disparate section about a single
contributor after the creation.

Change-Id: I412107ebdb288563b731cbfbf4f9483b89917b40
Closes-Bug: #1477418

Doc samples to rst

  Added 2 scripts for generating rst from samples
  Updated tox 'docs' env section for this operation
  Edited some README files to improve appearance

commit_message:
Fix diskimage-builder image size

This patch fixes the calculation of the resultant image size
when building an image with diskimage-builder on ext4 a
filesystem.

Prior to this, using the '--image-size 2' (2GB) setting would
generate an image that would not boot under a 2GB nova flavor.

Change-Id: I7a753bdef84c6300ccea73ae4a92bf330dcd77cb
Closes-Bug: #1513622

From a security perspective, what you are doing here has a pretty big flaw. And since this is all about security we need to talk about it.

The main purpose of this patch to to drop privileges for the running process. However by making the run_command file modifiable by the user running say the glance-api service, you open up a security hole in which the user itself can determine what process or application launches.

commit_message:
Prepare base images for USER operation

The base images need some changess to implement the USER operaton.
Files must be written to a file/directory owned by USER.  Previously
control files were in / which works for most cases, but not the
/configured file which is now written to /var/lib/kolla/configured.

Change-Id: I2112b02ecea9a5a43dd16cadf200e4c57ac4bd43
Partially-Implements: blueprint drop-root

commit_message:
Drop root privileges for glance services

note this cannot go in glance-base because the chmod 755 operates on
the file as root and a duplicate chown to glance would be needed in
glance-api and glance-registry.

Change-Id: I923748e59ef77e983b51dfb3bbf896f407aca149
Partially-Implements: blueprint drop-root

commit_message:
Drop root privileges for heat services

note this cannot go in heat-base because the chmod 755 operates on
the file as root and a duplicate chown to heat would be needed in
the children containers.

Change-Id: Ie80e2ea93dfe46a29fc1830ac7edbb55af596826
Partially-Implements: blueprint drop-root

Easier use of the initial start script. Less needs to be done with sudo to accomplish tasks since the main start script runs as root.

commit_message:
Fix agent_ilo to remove temporary images

agent_ilo driver doesn't cleanup the temporary
files created. This commit makes sure
that the temporary files are cleaned up before
the server goes for second boot.

Closes-bug: #1503795

Change-Id: I6cce1d1f3a5631e1af992c173379927fed3c55a1
(cherry picked from commit e34c4248af5f453a776af8b3933c5d7ece1c7b9c)

[{'created': '2015-11-09 01:23:18.000000000', 'message': 'Move devlib packages into "general"

The removal of the wheel caching code
(Ia140dc34638d893b92f66d1ba20efd9522c5923b) removed the install of the
"devlib" packages, which was being done with a call in
tools/build_wheels.sh

The idea of "devlibs" and "general" seems to be pretty much the same
thing -- global build requirements.  I have removed the unused devlibs
files, and moved any missing packages into the "general" package
install file.

Change-Id: I8f34a164d6785a122394b42387d4221a7b447ae1
'}]
commit_message:
Move devlib packages into "general"

The removal of the wheel caching code
(Ia140dc34638d893b92f66d1ba20efd9522c5923b) removed the install of the
"devlib" packages, which was being done with a call in
tools/build_wheels.sh

The idea of "devlibs" and "general" seems to be pretty much the same
thing -- global build requirements.  I have removed the unused devlibs
files, and moved any missing packages into the "general" package
install file.

Change-Id: I8f34a164d6785a122394b42387d4221a7b447ae1

commit_message:
Removes zone files when a zone is deleted

Add "-clean" option to "rndc delzone".
Note:
 The "-clean" option will take effect on bind>=9.10.0.

Change-Id: I911e929a6fea1d8c73a7247a8a574abb95335709
Closes-Bug: 1507243

commit_message:
Devstack: Use HOST_IP to set MAGNUM_SERVICE_HOST

Magnum k8s functional testing will try to access m-api inside of a VM, the
default setting of SERVICE_HOST is 127.0.0.1 which is not accessable from VM.

This patch use HOST_IP instead of SERVICE_HOST.

Closes-Bug: #1514286
o-Authored-By: OTSUKA, Yuanying<yuanying@fraction.jp>
Change-Id: Ic409818e5f85e6612390e490f4eeb17963bf3805

[{'created': '2015-10-29 14:52:16.000000000', 'message': 'cautiously fail on unhandled heartbeat exception

Currently, BaseAgentVendor.hearbeat handles uncaught exceptions by
advancing FSM with the "failed" event[1]. However, there are couple of
issues with this approach: 1) not all states support fail event (esp.
DEPLOYFAILED[2]) 2) with some states, the *FAILED state does not make sense
for the FSM to transition into upon uncaught exception (CLEAN* [3]) 3) some
driver interfaces may handle "failing" while raising exceptions[4], too
(iscsi_deploy)

The suggested patch purpose is to advance the FSM only in case an exception
happened while in either DEPLOYWAIT or DEPLOYING states to avoid FSM jam
while handling the exception[4]

[1] https://github.com/openstack/ironic/blob/master/ironic/drivers/modules/
      agent_base_vendor.py#L372
[2] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/ironic/_images/states.svg
[3] https://github.com/openstack/ironic/blob/master/ironic/drivers/modules/
      agent_base_vendor.py#L369
[4] https://bugs.launchpad.net/ironic/+bug/1506376

Change-Id: Ie2498bcb095535a25e46cea78365c2bfa4562d66
Closes-Bug: #1506376

commit_message:
cautiously fail on unhandled heartbeat exception

Currently, BaseAgentVendor.hearbeat handles uncaught exceptions by
advancing FSM with the 'failed' event no matter the state. Having
encountered an error, some drivers may both advance FSM themselves and
raise an exception. This leads to advancing the FSM with the 'fail' event
while already in the DEPLOYFAIL state.

Suggested patch purpose is to advance the FSM only if either in DEPLOYWAIT
or DEPLOYING state.

Change-Id: Ie2498bcb095535a25e46cea78365c2bfa4562d66
Closes-Bug: #1506376

commit_message:
Fix argument order in assertEqual to (expect, obs)

assertEqual expects that the arguments provided to it should be
(expected, observed). If a particular order is kept as a convention,
then it helps to provide a cleaner message to the developer if Unit Tests
fail. There are several Unit Test files where the arguments for assertEqual
have been swapped.

Change-Id: I6fdedcde67f76883257d35d1b812ab8a0e3e0733
Related-Bug: #1259292

Switch to oslo.reports

Oslo_reports enables OpenStack projects to dump Guru Meditation
Reports with useful debugging information to files or stderr.

Cleanup message handling in test_exception

There were unnecessary uses of six.text_type() in these tests
which made them more complicated than necessary.

commit_message:
Make puppet manifests compliant with Puppet 4.x

- https://docs.puppetlabs.com/puppet/3.8/reference/deprecated_language.html
- Temporary disablement of the pupppet-lint autoload layout check
  failing for ringbuilder.pp. A fix for that will be part of an other patch.

Change-Id: I495825641ab12e7c5789c1405649c356c5bb8051
Signed-off-by: Gael Chamoulaud <gchamoul@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Don't raise bare Exceptions

It's generally recommended that base Exceptions not be raised,
because this makes it impossible to handle exceptions in a more
granular way.  except Exception: will catch all exceptions, not
just the one you might care about.

This replaces most instances of this pattern in tripleoclient, with
the exception of the one in overcloud_image.py because I have a
separate change open that already fixes it.

Change-Id: I6fce306c4ffc57b4c52389be1feb583f5a400a64

commit_message:
Env var to allow building images for HA deployment

For corosync to be able to set up a cluster using hostnames as in
recommended HA architecture, we need to prevent cloud-init from
assigning FQDN to an IP on loopback interface.

https://bugs.launchpad.net/tripleo/+bug/1447497

Change-Id: I0aa6081902a5c17078739ec24f6666d803548ff0

[{'created': '2015-11-09 18:05:40.000000000', 'message': "Fix Horizon undercloud UI login

There were 2 issues causing problems logging into the undercloud UI.

First, when SSL was enabled, Horizon was failing to login with the self
signed cert because it's configured to use the publicURL endpoints. This
reconfigures Horizon to use the internalURL endpoints which are always
non-SSL.

Secondly, grant the admin user the admin role in the service project
since no project is specified when logging to the tuskar ui, and the
admin role is always required and we have no way to control what project
will be looked at if one isn't specified. See the bugzilla for more
details.

"}]
commit_message:
Fix Horizon undercloud UI login

There were 2 issues causing problems logging into the undercloud UI.

First, when SSL was enabled, Horizon was failing to login with the self
signed cert because it's configured to use the publicURL endpoints. This
reconfigures Horizon to use the internalURL endpoints which are always
non-SSL.

Secondly, grant the admin user the admin role in the service project
since no project is specified when logging to the tuskar ui, and the
admin role is always required and we have no way to control what project
will be looked at if one isn't specified. See the bugzilla for more
details.

Change-Id: I688b40601359641e8963e6655e1ecf86dfa90792
Resolves: rhbz#1245169

commit_message:
Fix simple bug in text formatter excluded files list

This commit fixes a simple bug in the verbose output listing for
the text formatter.  The formatter was erroneously outputting
skipped files (which should be a tuple) when it meant to be
outputting the excluded files.

Change-Id: I14eb69ad7e4848c79abbd15265d94c044f621816
Closes-Bug: #1514513

[{'created': '2015-11-06 13:10:35.000000000', 'message': "Improving Bandit Baseline Reporting

This commit changes the Bandit Baseline reporting functionality.
The previous behavior was to compare each file and if the issue
total was different we'd output all of the issues from the file.

While this worked to implement a gate it wasn't easy to use for
penetration testing and the report generated could be difficult
for developers to parse to figure out why the gate broke.

The new approach will pair down the issues to determine exactly
which were not present in the baseline.  Next since code lines
can move aorund we can't figure out exactly where in the file
the issue is, but we can present a list of candidate issues.

A candidate issue matches the core properties of the finding
including file, severity, confidence, and issue text.

Since we're now presenting candidate issues for each finding we
also need a way to display that.  Baseline will now use separate
specifically designed formatters that show candidate issues.

Change-Id: Id5aa45ac4977e84f1c08a6b8e142acc6e5fc7a88

commit_message:
Improving Bandit Baseline Reporting

This commit changes the Bandit Baseline reporting functionality.
The previous behavior was to compare each file and if the issue
total was different we'd output all of the issues from the file.

While this worked to implement a gate it wasn't easy to use for
penetration testing and the report generated could be difficult
for developers to parse to figure out why the gate broke.

The new approach will pair down the issues to determine exactly
which were not present in the baseline.  Next since code lines
can move aorund we can't figure out exactly where in the file
the issue is, but we can present a list of candidate issues.

A candidate issue matches the core properties of the finding
including file, severity, confidence, and issue text.

Since we're now presenting candidate issues for each finding we
also need a way to display that.  Baseline will now use separate
specifically designed formatters that show candidate issues.

Change-Id: Id5aa45ac4977e84f1c08a6b8e142acc6e5fc7a88

commit_message:
3PAR drivers volume size conversion is incorrect

The 3PAR drivers conversion of the volume size to gibibytes (GiBs) is
incorrect, resulting in slightly smaller volumes than expected. The
drivers were assuming the input was gigabytes (GBs) when in fact the
input was gibibytes (GiBs) as documented by the cinder API.

Change-Id: I5c86f506790723195f8f9433c9e5eedddd53a4ab
Closes-bug: 1513158

commit_message:
Add ConsistencyGroup for cinder v2

WADL file is newly created.
But its close API document exists on Shared File Systems API.

Ref
Consistencygroups spec
https://github.com/openstack/cinder-specs/blob/master/specs/juno/consistency-groups.rst

Shared File Systems API
http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-share-v2.html#consistency-groups

Partial-Bug: #1411724
Change-Id: I4ff4aa8511bcba4e3cbcb4a9618fbced9542248c

Thanks for the review Dave,
After looking into it more I think I need to do a little bit more investigation. There are several tests that modify the CONF variable (found in barbican/common/config.py and it is an instance of oslo_config.cfg.ConfigOpts()). But it is only restored inside barbican/tests/common/test_utils.py which doesn't use set_override(). I'm going to investigate more how this value is carried throughout the unit tests."}, {'account_id': 17579, 'date': '2015-10-15 15:29:54.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 17579, 'date': '2015-10-15 15:34:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

After further investigation, it seems that when tests are ran in parallel they are ran in different processes so they shouldn't share the same memory. But what does happen is that the same config.CONF is carried throughout the tests.
After using testr's bisection feature, I have found that a test inside test_validators was causing the other tests to fail. I have changed test_validators to use set_override() instead of direct assignment."}, {'account_id': 17579, 'date': '2015-10-15 15:36:27.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-15 16:38:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Verified+1

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-13 19:27:28.000000000', 'message': "Change localhost host_href references in unittests to use config.CONF

On some machines that have devstack installed, the host_href variable
inside /etc/barbican.conf is set to a non 'http://localhost' value
(http://10.0.2.15 for virtualbox). The tests inside
barbican/tests/common/test_validators.py fail due to a race condition
on the host_href variable on barbican.common.config.CONF. The two test
files, test_validators.py and test_utils.py both modify the CONF variable.
The tests inside test_validators override the host_href variable to be
localhost. This causes a problem since the tests run in parallel
because test_utils restores the value to non localhost. The
test_validators tests is now changed to get the host_href
variable directly from config.CONF instead of overriding the
variable. A test inside test_containers.py had to be changed
as well since it was dependent on the localhost host_href override
from the test_validators setup().

Change-Id: Icb24737ad1cda097803fe30a5a000f8591f183f4
Closes-bug: #1505315

"}, {'created': '2015-10-15 15:29:54.000000000', 'message': "Change unit tests in test_utils.py and test_contaiers.py to use CONF.set_override

On some machines that have devstack installed, the host_href variable
inside /etc/barbican.conf is set to a non 'http://localhost' value
(http://10.0.2.15 for virtualbox). When test_utils.py sets the host_href
variable, it causes other tests to fail because it causes set_override
to not work. When test_validators overrides the host_href variable it gets
back the CONF variable instead of the override. To fix this problem,
test_utils.py should also use set_override. The tests inside
test_containers are also missing the set_override.

Change-Id: Icb24737ad1cda097803fe30a5a000f8591f183f4
Closes-bug: #1505315

commit_message:
Change unit tests in test_utils.py and test_contaiers.py to use CONF.set_override

On some machines that have devstack installed, the host_href variable
inside /etc/barbican.conf is set to a non 'http://localhost' value
(http://10.0.2.15 for virtualbox). When test_utils.py sets the host_href
variable, it causes other tests to fail because it causes set_override
to not work. When test_validators overrides the host_href variable it gets
back the CONF variable (non localhost value) instead of
the override. To fix this problem, test_utils.py should
also use set_override and use clear_override. The tests inside
test_containers are also missing the set_override and clear_override.

Change-Id: Icb24737ad1cda097803fe30a5a000f8591f183f4
Closes-bug: #1505315

commit_message:
Add v2 support for optional project_id in version discovery urls

This is part of the work to allow Nova and Novaclient to handle endpoints both
with and without project id's. v2 version information returns a different data
structure than later versions. This patch updates the mock tests to return a
different data structure corresponding to v2 or v2.x depending on the
endpoint_type. A caller using the mock test class can set the attribute
endpoint_type to a version number, and the method get_endpoint, will return the
appropriate data structure. This is more of a workaround given the current state
of mocking Nova api calls in our unit tests.

Part of bp:service-catalog-tng

Change-Id: I61984ee592f7a5d7f1a91c9e2ff3038c0245f797

[{'created': '2015-11-08 21:40:12.000000000', 'message': 'drop root for glance

This uses the grouping feature of sudo to limit the amount of times
the base sudo file has to be modified to only once.  The container
contents always runs as the user root, except the softwaer which is
controlled by Kolla.  This software may run as root, but it has
undergone a security audit and preserves permissions of the correct

commit_message:
drop root for glance

This uses the grouping feature of sudo to limit the amount of times
the base sudo file has to be modified to only once.  The container
contents always runs as the user root, except the software which is
controlled by Kolla.  This software may run as root, but it has
undergone a security audit and preserves permissions of the correct
files and does not permit the glance user to write any of the
set_config.py control files.

Change-Id: Ie3cd23edcde5b408a8f66970456279a1b15028e0
Partially-Implements: blueprint drop-root

commit_message:
Base image changes for drop-root

The reason we are doing drop root is so that a network exposed
software component (i.e. glance) cannot be used to affect the
immutability of the container which it runs in.  I have tried
several different approaches and this is the only approach which
puts glance in PID=1 while ensuring no files may be written by
the glance process in the container image except for the log files.

Change-Id: Ifd3c8c361b78d0e4791dade3afa6435290407c41
Partially-Implements: blueprint drop-root

commit_message:
Allow scripts-library.sh to be sourced anywhere

Currently, we cannot source scripts-library.sh from anywhere outside of
the top-level of the openstack-ansible checkout.  This behaviour
changed with commit d9b9a427aa03f866458bdffc220c596c7b4b5bb2.

This commit itself updates scripts-library.sh to use $BASH_SOURCE to
find the location of os-detection.py, allowing scripts-library.sh to
be sourced from any external project without having to cd into the
openstack-ansible checkout and back out again.

Change-Id: Ia5cec5a0f1af4f8d4998465923077c87ffaf24ef
Closes-Bug: #1510443
(cherry picked from commit b5a6381457bce88413b4c6865f929ef086297d18)

A change from the "Remove dir_mode from rabbit key distribution" commit caused
a bug where non-primary RabbitMQ containers would keep /etc/rabbitmq
permissions set to 0750 (the default is 0755).  This prevented the plugins
file from being read and it broke queue mirroring.

This patch ensures that the default permission of 0755 is set on RabbitMQ
and should prevent problems with future upgrades.

Closes-bug: 1513668

'}]
commit_message:
Fixing /etc/rabbitmq permission bug

A change from the "Remove dir_mode from rabbit key distribution" commit caused
a bug where non-primary RabbitMQ containers would keep /etc/rabbitmq
permissions set to 0750 (the default is 0755).  This prevented the plugins
file from being read and it broke queue mirroring.

This patch ensures that the default permission of 0755 is set on RabbitMQ
and should prevent problems with future upgrades.

Closes-bug: 1513668

Change-Id: I62d6b09dad0eef0d9543442bb727f6c946d8738e

commit_message:
Enable custom instance size for Tempest flavors in local config

This patch enables DEFAULT_INSTANCE_TYPE=custom and also introduces
a new parameter CUSTOM_INSTANCE_SIZE=XXX to create custom flavors
for Tempest tests. The motivation behind this change is that micro
and nano flavors are too small for some platforms, so it gives more
flexibility to the users. Using the default instances types available
would make Tempest to create a huge alternative flavor for the resize
scenarios. The custom flavor behavior creates an alternative flavor
with CUSTOM_INSTANCE_SIZE+128MB.

DocImpact

Change-Id: Ic183cc0f5e6cf5eda914cc8b03e76ac2d971bf31

I like this plan, but I think the blueprint needs to address how we actually do the refactor. For example, I think we should hold the standard for help strings in the new common files deliberately very high, and that part of moving the flags across to those modules is adding the missing documentation.

I know this makes the refactor harder, but it also makes it obvious what is at the new documentation standard and what isn't. I'm not super excited by code churn reviews which move things around, whilst a series of reviews that move things while improving the documentation does excite me.

That might also mean this naturally breaks things up so that more people help out -- to write that documentation you need to understand the underlying code, which means that local experts will be needed."}, {'account_id': 11303, 'date': '2015-10-08 13:40:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Nova has around 800 config options [1]. Those config options are the
interface to the cloud operators. Unfortunately they often lack a
good documentation which

commit_message:
Centralize Config Options

Nova has around 800 config options [1]. Those config options are the
interface to the cloud operators. Unfortunately they often lack a
good documentation which
* explains their impact,
* shows their interdependency to other config options and
* explains which of the Nova services they influence.
This cloud operator interface needs to be consolidated and one way of
doing this is, to move the config options from their declaration in
multiple modules to a few centrally managed modules. These centrally
managed modules should also provide the bigger picture of the
configuration surface we provide. This got already discussed on the
ML [2].

[1] see the "nova.flagmappings" file which get generated in the
    "openstack-manuals" project for the "configuration reference" 
    manual.
[2]
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-July/070306.html

Implements blueprint centralize-config-options

Change-Id: I182e368dd2896aad643f539e7bb2493daf5ead5c

commit_message:
Remove deployment mode support

Different deployment mode was deprecated in Fuel 6.1. The
current and newer versions of python-fuelclient are not
compatible with that version of Fuel.

This patch removes all options and mentions of the deprecated
feature.

Change-Id: Ieeadc43592bd72cb813a0aa914779bd4cfe13586
Closes-bug: #1441129

commit_message:
Plumb fixed_address through add_ips_to_server

Specifying a fixed_address if you know it is somethig that the lower
level functions understand, but was left out of the argument list
for add_ips_to_server. Plumb it through.

Change-Id: Iba3456f0f45e5b0230c752a50fc3d3b29e8ade54

commit_message:
Add unit tests around JobController

As part of building a reliable UI, I am including tests around our
core components.

commit_message:
Boot slaves after creation of custom nodegroup

Since DHCP server for additional admin/pxe networks
is configured after nodegroup creation, we can't
bootstrap slaves until we created cluster and setup
its networks.
Also align 'hacks' for multiple cluster networks
tests with dynamic dnsmasq feature.

Change-Id: I46b203d65a2fe2f0bb41288aaf8fb738d2bda495
Implements: blueprint align-nodegroups-tests
Related-bug: #1495593

Use oslo_config PortOpt type for port options

The oslo.config>=2.6.0 library provides new PortOpt type to validate
a range of port.

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-17 22:11:09.000000000', 'message': "Update to use os-client-config and keystoneauth1

keystoneauth1 is the new auth-only library for getting keystone
Sessions, which is lighter-weight and does not require the entire
keystoneclient library. It also handles all of the keystone
version discover and plugin selection so that code doesn't have to
live in neutronclient.

Additionally, use os-client-config to process options and get the
Session from keystoneauth1. This adds support for reading clouds.yaml
files and supporting the OS_CLOUD env var for selecting named clouds
from a list of them.

Remove the auth tests - since they are covered inside of ksa.

Change-Id: Ic4f9fd8f231c33513fd74da58ab1b4a3fb00d9f4

commit_message:
Use os-client-config and keystoneauth1 in shell

keystoneauth1 is the new auth-only library for getting keystone
Sessions, which is lighter-weight and does not require the entire
keystoneclient library. It also handles all of the keystone
version discover and plugin selection so that code doesn't have to
live in neutronclient.

Additionally, use os-client-config to process options and get the
Session from keystoneauth1. This adds support for reading clouds.yaml
files and supporting the OS_CLOUD env var for selecting named clouds
from a list of them.

This is a step towards bug#1503428 but is not the whole picture.

Remove the auth tests - since they are covered inside of ksa.

Closes-Bug: #1507384
Change-Id: Ic4f9fd8f231c33513fd74da58ab1b4a3fb00d9f4

Making desc parameter of update_image optional

description should be passed no matter provided
descr parameter or not to make this change
backward compatible

commit_message:
Drop cliff-tablib from test-requirements.txt

tablib has no support on Py3 and it is a blocker of Py3 support.
In my understanding, cliff-tablib is not required for testing,
so I think we can drop cliff-tablib safely.

Change-Id: I6734a01028545d8bd2cd0950b66cc1714b3ae291

commit_message:
Add functional tests for tlds

The tld tests will create/remove tlds which would cause problems
when running zone tests in parallel. To solve this, a separate tld
is created for each zone.

Change-Id: I8957f6f294bc5624ce049e36bef4a948cef3e380

commit_message:
Fix a bug where the temp folder is not always removed

When a CSAR file is processed its content is temporairly decompressed
into a temp folder that is supposed to gets wiped after processing is
complete. This patch fixes a bug where the folder is not always gets
wiped.

Change-Id: I219a6ab7054247e86972fc8c979c643c6184dace
Closes-Bug: #1503907

commit_message:
Use sum of volumes and snapshots for cinder usage

The cinder quota on gigabytes is the sum of both volumes and snapshots,
therefore in the horizon view we should be representing usage as the
combination of volumes and snapshots, otherwise users will be confused
when getting quota errors on volume or snapshot creation.

Closes-Bug: 1513179
Change-Id: Id23e0dd3a3f810e75f9013cecbf8a826c97e34c6
(cherry picked from commit 944c8bafdcf12d0a0dd56c6c43eab84f513d6e5f)

commit_message:
Check seamicro terminal port as long as it specified

We should do port check as long as it specified, but now it
happens only when 'if port', which will miss invalid parameter ''.

Closes-Bug: #1513845
Change-Id: I39400e5026098a7feb1108b412e16b4506f22b8d

commit_message:
Add self.raid for iSCSI based drivers

This commit adds self.raid = agent.AgentRAID()
for the drivers pxe_ipmitool, pxe_ipminative, pxe_ssh,
pxe_ilo, pxe_vbox. The same was done for agent drivers in
Ifa640d4839b2f08410ceec57c2972e2f9dc69db3.

It also adds test cases for these drivers which were
missing.

Change-Id: I5e7046ec56dd851a197da8571bd933cabd3dd210
Implements: blueprint inband-raid-configuration

commit_message:
Refactoring of ModuleHelper

  * split ModuleHelper.screenUI method
  * add enum for widget types
  * use field 'type' instead of 'value' to provide widget type

Related to blueprint dynamically-build-bootstrap-fuel-menu

Change-Id: If6f68434727c7384b6cdb38a8ea82d0cf1e6c452

commit_message:
Switch to stable release branches

The stable/liberty branch of ceilometer-powervm should be paired to the
release/1.0.0 branch of pypowervm and the stable ceilometer branch.

Change-Id: I3bd546cfa9eeddc39cfa0017368741b254427cd3

commit_message:
Switch to develop branch for pypowervm

The master branch of nova-powervm should be paired to the 'develop'
branch of pypowervm.

Other stable branches (or release candidates) will point to version
levels that are published to PyPi (or to stable branches).

Change-Id: I963e20da759eeede6b1f115d15fdc276b3555538

commit_message:
Switch to develop branch for pypowervm

The master branch of ceilometer-powervm should be paired to the
'develop' branch of pypowervm.

Other stable branches (or release candidates) will eventually point to
version levels that are published to PyPi (or to stable branches).

Change-Id: I4ba962acb322851b982689bb50958769be21c53c

commit_message:
Fix /NetworkDriver.CreateEndpoint validation

In Interface properties, Address and AddressIPv6 are coming as empty
strings from libnetwork and that is breaking current validation logic.
Logic is added to accept empty string also for mac and ipv4 address.

Change-Id: Ib32bee76c6add1c5af616b7d74b346eef906fa8b
Closes-Bug: #1507508

commit_message:
Add a note to docs about parameter defaults

Document that the client will now use most defaults from the Heat
templates, rather than be hardcoded in the client. Environment files
are the proper way to override these defaults.

Change-Id: Ifd740c50ee0e48e0cf50d9ebd9cc282155cb3a6d

commit_message:
Workaround a dispute between osc and neutronclient

python-openstackclient wants network_api_version to be 2. neutronclient
wants it to be 2.0. There is a patch to OSC to make it understand both,
but in the mean time, let's unbreak people.

Change-Id: I4d8f187d1302c5bcfa246e017e6c6d8af9c3f733

commit_message:
Add option for repetitions in repeat-test.sh

This patch adds a new option '-r' to limit the number of repetitions
done by repeat-test.sh. The default remains an endless loop.

Change-Id: I85ffdca16dab8b747448d87ef4266b17a9bf64ba

commit_message:
Be more verbose when getting log files after testing

This patch adds some additional console output to get_upstart_logs.sh
(used by repeat-test.sh) to inform the user about the script's progress.

[{'created': '2015-11-05 04:28:22.000000000', 'message': 'restore-cluster: skip non-existent VMs

The restore-cluster.sh tool aborts if a VM from VM_LIST does not exist.
Therefore, the script breaks if the cluster building never managed to
create all VMs in the list.

This patch lets the script skip non-existent VMs.

Change-Id: I0e0fd2dea9f582f1def0f734f10e4656d98394c6
'}]
commit_message:
restore-cluster: skip non-existent VMs

The restore-cluster.sh tool aborts if a VM from VM_LIST does not exist.
Therefore, the script breaks if the cluster building never managed to
create all VMs in the list.

This patch lets the script skip non-existent VMs.

Change-Id: I0e0fd2dea9f582f1def0f734f10e4656d98394c6

commit_message:
Add custom package apt provides with timeout

It may be that dkpg database is locked by abother process during
the Puppet run. Consequently, the deployment will fail.
To mitigate the issue, it is possible to wrap default apt provider
with a class which waits until the lock is released or timeout
expired.

Change-Id: I691ca96cced232483fb2f3e79cbf3ee402f765ea
Fixes-bug: #1510107

commit_message:
Workaround for int value with verbose_level

python-openstackclient uses an int value for verbose level which the
stringification patch broke. As a quick fix, special case verbose_level,
as fixing it properly might take more than 5 minutes.

Change-Id: Ie12a40d3d3e400b3ec2103d7a58c4902fb10fc2d
Closes-Bug: #1513919

commit_message:
Fix handling of "current" target snapshot

An uninitialized variable caused restore-cluster.sh to abort with an
error if the user selected the current (rather than a named) snapshot.

Fixed.

Change-Id: I708110a2ba9f88b6879d8d4b604bed7e68a6b0ba

commit_message:
Add new dsl exception for better error reporting

Extend NoClassFound exception for the case when we have parent and child
MuranoPL classes in different packages and "parent" package is not
present in the requirements section of the "child" package.

Change-Id: I41b8033f7e987564ab804d9219eb5063b9e8320b
Closes-Bug: #1504334

commit_message:
Read vif port information in bulk

During startup, the agent was making many calls per port
to read information about the current VLAN, external ID, etc.
This resulted in hundreds of calls just to read information about
a relatively small number of ports.

This patch addresses that by converting a few key functions to
lookup information for all of the ports at once.

Performance improvement on dev laptop for 250 ports from agent
start to port ACTIVE status:
   before: 1m21s
   after: 1m06s

Closes-Bug: #1460233
Change-Id: Ic80c85a07fee3e5651dc19819c6cebdc2048dda7
(cherry pick-picked from commit 4dc68ea88bf4f07b13253bf9eeedffe22b1f8013)
Conflicts:
	neutron/agent/common/ovs_lib.py
	neutron/plugins/openvswitch/agent/ovs_neutron_agent.py
	neutron/tests/unit/plugins/ml2/drivers/openvswitch/agent/test_ovs_neutron_agent.py
	neutron/tests/unit/plugins/openvswitch/test_ovs_tunnel.py

commit_message:
Allow iscsi traffic only to cinder/iscsi ip

This traffic should be limited to iscsi IP on
storage network, not 0.0.0.0.

Added corresponding unit and noop tests for
coverage.

Change-Id: I8201c1120fbadad1edad520a51b06ca22d122bf2
Closes-Bug: #1501734

commit_message:
Adds error_code in heat exceptions

Tags a given exception with error code. It helps
to report or handle the exception based the code.

implements blueprint: heat-template-validate-improvements

Change-Id: Iea6599c1602e57ce4020303e56c839d1a6a8ac52

commit_message:
Disable command run under root user

Running openstack command with python-tripleoclient under
root user is not supported and should not be allowed. Added
check for user and exit if it is root (EUID=0) to openstack
undercloud install command.

Each command can be disabled for root by adding
utils.ensure_run_as_normal_user() into it's body.

Backport to stable/liberty of Change-Id: I685c639e02790483d1607c7eac038f8b9b8dc99e

Change-Id: I374a27ff4c7a16eb42dd474a7978a953aa9dbb80
Closes-Bug: rhbz#1239088

This was changed 5 days ago in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/237519/ Could you explain why this was wrong and update the commit message please ?'}, {'account_id': 17523, 'date': '2015-11-06 16:14:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Hi Jordan Pittier, thanks for your concern.
In L3NATAgentWithStateReport init method, it will import interface driver use this method `File "/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/oslo_utils/importutils.py", line 24, in import_class`.
Key code in this process is this line `mod_str, _sep, class_str = import_str.rpartition('.')`

import_str value is same as interface_driver.
So if interface_driver = openvswitch, mod_str and _sep would be null and error occurred.
l3 agent could start correctly use absolute interface driver path like neutron.agent.linux.interface.OVSInterfaceDriver.

Neutron is stable/liberty and complete debug log is here in attach file https://bugs.launchpad.net/devstack/+bug/1513684'}, {'account_id': 7350, 'date': '2015-11-06 16:24:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

You can't use devstack master to install neutron stable/liberty. This is not how this is supposed to work.

If you want to test/run neutron liberty you should checkout devstack liberty branch."}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2015-11-06 20:01:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

wait wait wait. The *old* way was a class import, and the new way is via aliases. 

See c5db6050e5c1988ba845d4b7e50d12057359f19f'}, {'account_id': 17523, 'date': '2015-11-09 13:58:38.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

not a bug'}]

commit_message:
Update the devref for volume migration

This patch proposes a thorough update to the development doc
for the volume migration. Several improvements to volume
migration have been made during the last development cycle
and this patch attempts to document the current state.

Change-Id: Ibe233d82a0694b29ecdf4abce4af735b34821c3f
Partial-implements: blueprint migration-improvement

commit_message:
Really get the "general" packages

We are specifying the argument to get_packages incorrectly, so we are
not actually adding the packages in "general" to the list of packages.

In most cases, this is hidden as other more specific plugins/services
request their packages.  However, as
I2dafd32f211fcbc9fff53030d736d97a5f1bb2df shows, not always.  I think
this was uncovered by 5f8133caac097235ed4fe73d878df0ee907eb51c

Change-Id: Ie1b8d09369281059d21da61b2725a457f708ae9e

- gate-tempest-lib-python34 http://logs.openstack.org/60/219560/2/check/gate-tempest-lib-python34/8c76147/ : SUCCESS in 1m 40s'}, {'account_id': 5196, 'date': '2015-09-02 15:59:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

So I'm on the fence about this, because we're essentially logging the same thing twice, once at info and then again at debug.
I understand the perspective about parallel execution not making info and debug right next to each other, but isn't that what
the request id is for, to correlate the logs from the same request. How do the services handle this because they log similar
info at debug and the high level request information at info?"}, {'account_id': 6167, 'date': '2015-09-03 05:36:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Hi Matt,

Thanks for your comment.
Yeah, the request id should work for knowing the combination, but I feel it is a small burden and I'd like to avoid it.
I also have the same feeling it is not smart that the same logs are output twice, but the debugging messages are redundant in many cases and I felt it was acceptable.

To avoid the same messages twice, it would be nice to merge them into a single as you said. but am afraid to do that, because INFO log will become big even if disabling debugging log output.

I have an experience someone did beat me on public mailing-list(openstack-dev) after I made the log much for debugging the gate problem. So I'd like to avoid the situation at this time."}, {'account_id': 6167, 'date': '2015-11-09 13:32:10.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

unnecessary now.'}]

commit_message:
Add common info to the REST debugging log

Current REST debugging log doesn't contain common info like status
code, http method and URL. They are output as the info log, and in
most case the info log is output just before the debugging log.
Developers can know the combination of them usually, but sometimes
it is difficult to know because the tests run in parallel.
This patch adds common info to the debugging log for knowing the
combination surelly.

Change-Id: I8c395384203fca4d842bcc117d221a227fa080f8

commit_message:
Make ironic-inspector and its client release:managed

Inspector is a subproject of ironic, we'd like to ask the release
team to handle its releases from now on. This change also clarifies
release tags for the client based on what is going on right now.

Change-Id: I9ef6d7ce64d6428276386d5e677a189da6eca8c7

commit_message:
Add missing group for keystone

This is not a requirement since keystone has a single host, but it
does give us a few things. It gives us unity across the playbook
roles and it allows us to add more services related to keystone if
there ever are any additional serivces without tripping over this bug
again.

TrivialFix
Related-Bug: #1513439
Related-Id: Iab88b49712828085e4d7e7f85e6d8f0b7999a9bf

Change-Id: If0a141c101c948a4c71f45a4c51b1bcfb6a44a4d

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be

    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

commit_message:
Update Octavia release model

Since Octavia is now the default reference implementation of LBaaS
V2, add the following tags to it:

- release:cycle-with-milestones
- release:has-stable-branches

We'll run this way for a single cycle and then try to move to
"release:managed" during Nxxx.

Change-Id: Ie778f5cd4a8a51e1617e1e82229866134c62eedd
Signed-off-by: Kyle Mestery <mestery@mestery.com>

commit_message:
Add support to tag patch port for Cisco Nexus1000v VSM bringup

In some deployments we will need to tag the patch port connecting to
vsm-br in order for traffic to go out. This patch takes passes the vlan
parameter to the puppet.

Change-Id: I18734ae39007985769db9371abe1740e0f2872f7

commit_message:
Do not resolve keystone values if it is None

In patch Ic7a3001ab271cad12f4fe45c0930562070a0d600 were added new
functions for resolving keystone values. However it may lead to an error,
when the user does not specify the related property and it's None.
These functions can not resolve None value and fail.
This patch adds check for None values.

Change-Id: I667e61e9553a92703dbc5a37a311d93c4a377d4b
Closes-Bug: #1509354

commit_message:
Add python-memcached to list of installed pkgs on controllers

We use memcached for a few services but can't rely on the python
module being installed as a dependency because it techincally isn't
needed unless one configures the services to use memcached.

More at: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1271433#c12

Change-Id: I462532ca49157b57b4a558922bd3cb2cbce103e6

commit_message:
Log a new tunnel endpoint being registered or updated

Sometimes we'd like to know why some tunnels are not created on a node.
It may be either an agent failing to report its (new) local_ip, or
server failing to notify other parties about a new endpoint to create.

To understand whether an agent actually hit the controller, it would be
great to have a (non-debug) logging message just for that on controller
side.

It should be fine to log new or existing agent updates in non-debug
log level since those events are not too often, so we should not expect
logs being flooded.

The patch adds to a debug log for _add_endpoint, logging with info level
when an agent is registered or updated.  It also reports the host name
and tunnel type in addition to IP address, and distinguishes between the
cases of a new, unknown, agent being registered, and an existing one
being updated.

Change-Id: I9b5f52db119d48078612b4c3d42e996d172a2dff

commit_message:
Deal with underscores in blacklist during generate-constraints

In change id  I60adf0dca4aa32f4ef6bca61250b375c8a3703c6, we added
flake8_docstrings to the black list. However as seen in
I8bfff1b2e65541959e7f2ae0fa6ca6c17889eb54, the generate-constraints
job ends up proposing adding "flake8-docstrings===0.2.1.post1" to
the upper-constraints.txt. This is because of the '-' vs '_'
difference. So just like in Ibaa22657a2cf2c0ad96dbd0b9bc43cdafe6a1d56,
we need to convert the items in black list to the correct safe name
before trying to check if the item is in the black list.

Change-Id: Ieb1cd44e908b80d58a20bf0d0e1e6b10f17ae95e

commit_message:
Fix dockerctl unlocking

* replace $FDLOCK with correct file descriptor
* do an unlock before attaching to a container – it never exits unless
  killed by supervisord
* correctly redirect error message to stderr
* remove /var/lock/dockerctl

Closes-bug: 1513422
Change-Id: Idd70c381632e3dca7c24edab78a731dc03f363e1

Add Mitaka project priorities

This adds a document laying out our priorities for the Mitaka cycle,
inspired by what Nova does. It also refactors the index page to add the
priorities tree.

commit_message:
Remove JSCS

ESLint evolved and become mature enough to completely replace
JSCS. This commit translates JSCS rules into ESLint ones and
fixes the code accordingly.

Also, ESLint config converted to YAML for readability

Change-Id: I2bea5b48284c68ecacd3ec3ac67c5852345f29e3

commit_message:
Make setup.py install Manila Tempest plugin

This commit makes the install directive in setup.py install the
Manila Tempest plugin when the rest of Manila is installed.

Closes-Bug: #1513953
Co-Author: Marc Koderer <marc@koderer.com>
Change-Id: Id2d75c2901e795ad1309cde275592d89f223471d

Flavors: use dict comprehension for get_all_flavors

Make use of dict comprehension to create the dictionary returned
by the aforementioned method.

TrivialFix

commit_message:
Enable "openstack server pause" command to take multiple servers.

Current "openstack server pause" command could only pause one server.
Improve it to be able to handle more than one servers. Also improve
the doc to reflect the new feature.

Change-Id: I809f77f0720457c9cdc1028a70b391c75885984c

commit_message:
Disable --save-only mode during post-deployment

It is common for users to run bootstrap_admin_node to apply
a patch to Fuel Master, which has the side effect of calling
fuelmenu --save-only --iface=ethN. This behavior initializes
all fields to defaults, which has negative consequences.

Now fuelmenu --save-only --iface=ethN will result in a message
saying that the user should run full fuelmenu in order to make
changes.

Moved get_deployment_mode to common.utils so it can be called
from save_only without expensive urwid imports.

Added unit tests for get_deployment_mode

Change-Id: I78d3261a5e2700b7533d9873f6bec9cc4e98c362
Closes-Bug: #1513486

commit_message:
Refine the overview.rst for sahara

The change document is
https://github.com/openstack/sahara/blob/master/doc/source/overview.rst
In the section of introduction,the description of key feature's
formate is not unified.The leading is bigger than others, and the
third point is overstriking.Why the line is overstriking?

Change-Id: I006ad5a887597a02a06b52784bd82b5bb863dbb2

commit_message:
Add ability validate yaml files before run tests

If you set flag --valiate in command for run tests,
scenario framework will be doing validating,
tests will not be runned

(1 comment)

No time for a full review tonight, sorry.

The code in horizon/tables/base.py, with its liberal use of str(), text_type and utf-8 multiple times in the one method which is deep inside our code (nowhere near anything that should be doing encoding or decoding) has thrown up some alarm bells. Those decodings need to be dealt with before I'll +1 this patch.

The lookup value, as far as I can tell, only comes from one place, BatchAction.handle() and if I trace that back through multiple() and single() both invoke the method with object_ids from a POST which, as far as I'm aware, will *always* be a unicode object. This that first condition's body should never be executed (if it was, it'd clearly break on anything that's not ASCII, and probably result in bizarro behaviour in py3 if a bytes object was passed in, not that it ever would...)

The object ids in self.data are likely to sometimes be integers, but more likely they *should* be unicode objects (py2) or strings (py3) [I'm going to assume at the moment that self.data is basically verbatim from the underlying client API and that doesn't necessarily Do The Right Thing, something I'm going to be looking into I hope]. Either way, it's probably safe to keep that code as-is, with some thought to cleaning up the py2 case so it doesn't barf if we ever do have a high-codepoint object id unicode object come back in the data "UnicodeDecodeError: ASCII has no idea what you're doing" ;-)

I offer my services to look into this more fully tomorrow, if it's not addressed overnight.'}, {'account_id': 12071, 'date': '2015-10-08 06:30:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Actually, I just realised, that the py3 code branch in the bit I'm talking about will break since str(b'id') is "b'id'" and not 'id' as it would be in py2...'}, {'account_id': 9107, 'date': '2015-10-09 07:09:24.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 9107, 'date': '2015-10-09 07:12:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

I modified my code to use the new oslo_serialization.jsonutils.dump_as_bytes() function.

Richard Jones: "The code in horizon/tables/base.py, with its liberal use of str(), text_type and utf-8 multiple times in the one method which is deep inside our code"

I reworked the code to accept any type on Python 3. By the way, I ran tox -e py34 using python3 -bb to catch more Unicode versus bytes issue. For example, str(b'bytes') fails with a BytesWarning. And the tests pass.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-09 08:02:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

[{'created': '2015-10-06 14:48:24.000000000', 'message': "py3: Fix unicode versus bytes issues

* DataTable: don't try to decode Unicode from UTF-8. Only decode on
  Python 2.
* On Python 3, explicitly encode JSON to UTF-8.
* Decode HTTP body from UTF-8 to decode JSON.
* Fix unit tests: HTTP body type is bytes.
* Container tests: use a named temporary file, the function handling
  the filename fails. On Python 3, TemporaryFile() uses a number for
  the filename: the file descriptor.
* Don't encode filename to UTF-8 on Python 3, keep Unicode.
* tox.ini: add 2 admin tests on Python 3.4.

Partial-Implements: blueprint porting-python3
Change-Id: Ib7e2cb17f20474590fac18faf8116131692ad694

commit_message:
py3: Fix unicode versus bytes issues

* DataTable: don't try to decode Unicode from UTF-8. Only decode on
  Python 2.
* Use oslo_serialization.jsonutils.dump_as_bytes() to encode JSON
  as bytes.
* Use oslo_serialization.jsonutils.loads() instead of json.loads() to
  accept bytes string as input. On Python 3, json.loads() only
  accepts Unicode string.
* Fix unit tests: HTTP body type is bytes.
* Container tests: use a named temporary file, the function handling
  the filename fails. On Python 3, TemporaryFile() uses a number for
  the filename: the file descriptor.
* Don't encode filename to UTF-8 on Python 3, keep Unicode.
* tox.ini: add 2 admin tests on Python 3.4.

Partial-Implements: blueprint porting-python3
Change-Id: Ib7e2cb17f20474590fac18faf8116131692ad694

commit_message:
Rename .jsx files to .js

Since we use Babel to transform JSX and Webpack for bundling,
ti doesn't make sense anymore to keep a separate .jsx extension
for files.

Change-Id: If70b512d7a27684d2b9b84b24f19658294cc1505

commit_message:
Disable py34 for networking-cisco kilo and juno

Stable kilo and juno did not support python 3.4 so there is no point
testing it against those branches. This is blocking patches merging
into our stable branches.

Change-Id: I36857354374cb12189eac64dc1c9d9120c8c87f4

commit_message:
Initial commit for service broker tests in tempest plugin

- Add tempest plugin structure
- Add basic functional for tempest service broker REST client
- Add config opts for application catalog and service broker API services
- Add base for service broker tests
- Add service broker test for list applications
- Add tempest plugin configure function into devstack murano plugin

Change-Id: If4c8f95a9d69fccf6f261510b6e02eb67c738ee5
Targets: blueprint murano-cfapi-func-tests

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-11-06 14:39:32.000000000', 'message': 'Fix race condition with router creation

Previously when murano deployed a bunch of environments from scratch
it was possible to have an error during router creation. Router was
created by env_1 and before it was fully configure it was accessed by

commit_message:
Fix race condition with router creation

Previously when murano deployed a bunch of environments from scratch
it was possible to have an error during router creation. Router was
created by env_1 and before it was fully configure it was accessed by
env_2 and then the error occurred.

Change-Id: I6936a2c46bf41c68e4aceca4a333723a27165071
Closes-Bug: #1493883

commit_message:
Add CLI tests for environment redeploy

- Added test that checks that it is possible to add app to the
deployed environment and redeploy it
- Added test that checks that it is possible to delete app from
the deployed environment and redeploy it
- Compose neeeded for deployment steps in the one method called
'deploy_environment' to avoid code duplication
- Added 'generate_uuid' method for application id generation

Partially implements: blueprint cli-tests-coverage-improvement

Change-Id: I6cbc718efa0d4eb0c5128b7a1d9637c386acbc74

commit_message:
Incorrect parsed variable name

database_user_create was not correctly referenced when parsing the
variable names. This could never actually lead to a situation that
reported a false change, but it could break an operation if you were
using the --step option with ansible and skipped the database create
task.

TrivialFix
Backport: Liberty

Change-Id: Idf69fffcc3814f509448ccea11b7d175f074ccf1

commit_message:
heat: remove legacy functional jobs

heat have moved its functional tests to aodh instead of
ceilometer-alarm.

This change removes the legacy tests that uses ceilometer-alarm.

Change-Id: I99c9f2be0bbc70f289da5c2ba22698b8b7dc4495

commit_message:
Add new pipeline for magnum

This patch splits one functional testing pipeline to api(common) and
k8s.

We should merge this patch first, then
Ic33ea42f6108c7444c152706458cf1a686ed1756 would works well.

Partially implements: blueprint split-gate-functional-dsvm-magnum
Change-Id: I10e09b2deea7a0643a9516701994cc47813e1aaa

commit_message:
Add dsvm into job names for Kolla

clarkb suggested dsvm be in the job names for Kolla to follow the
job naming convention. In the case of the experimental job we have
recently merged, that it as a requirement for the name of the job.

To keep consistency within the project and within the OpenStack
community we are renaming all of the gates that use the dsvm's to the
convention that all other jobnames follow.

Since the tox paramaters do not change in the jobs/kolla.yaml, this
requires no change on the Kolla side.

commit_message:
remove default=None for config options

In the cfg module default=None is set as the default value.
It's not necessary to set it again when defining config options.

Change-Id: I1da2192df37b7e460e63bb59cd7d691aa9be00f4
Closes-bug: #1323975

commit_message:
Add custom docker registry to DockerStandaloneHost

Allow access to private docker registry using docker argument
'--insecure-registry'.
Add new field for docker private registry host ip or domain name.

Partially implements: blueprint k8s-docker-enterprise-hub-support

Change-Id: I0e7b0ceebe9deda090fff56ec87f3c615050cc2a

Install bigswitch networking plugin by default

Install the bigswitch networking packages
python-networking-bigswitch
openstack-neutron-bigswitch-lldp

commit_message:
Introduce Murano extended logging class

There is a range of extended logging options in Openstack services that use
openstack.common.logger (Ceilometer, Cinder, Heat, Keystone, Nova).
Adding murano::logging to support them like it done for puppet-heat,
puppet-ceilometer, puppet-cinder, etc.

Change-Id: I0139cff7ae729381ffb2f9535fa74912d54fa4af

commit_message:
Allowing shares to be edited on cluster update

In order to allow the shares to be updated on a running
cluster, the cluster update operation has been updated
to allow the shares element.

Change-Id: I33971eb495c5a318ba17a4b3f98534b9e8776deb
Partial-Implements: bp sahara-add-shares-to-clusters

commit_message:
Add functional api tests for categories

- Added positive and negative tempest api tests for work with
categories
- Change inheritance: made separate class for authorisation, made
separate class that will contain methods for object creation (and
cleanup for them). Lately all methods for object creation will be
moved to this class and will use right cleanup mechanism (instead of
current implementation when objects save in array). This change was
made in this commit to avoid using incorrect solution in new tests.

Implements: blueprint tempest-tests-for-categories-management

Change-Id: I1fe71e385ab62c1d9fb9a9d90dd44f453aa953a9

commit_message:
[config-ref] tables: update some incorrect values

The autohelp script didn't properly clean some values. Use sensible
values for pybasedir-based paths instead of values related to the build
environment.

Change-Id: Id72eef4436a5edeb67adced9169824adb4d4aa3f

commit_message:
Support shares in sahara node group templates

Since 0.10.0 python-saharaclient has ability to specify
shares parameter when creating node group templates.
This patch adds support for this feature to
OS::Sahara::NodeGroupTemplate resource in Heat.

Change-Id: I055dd09ae4f452fb04bb9e42d7651e279bc0710b

commit_message:
Don't configure Cobbler while using nodegroups

Since automatic Cobbler (DHCP) configuration is
implemented for nodegroups we don't need to do
that in tests anymore.

Change-Id: I53798807489b7db421af446ce37e203ea04e1e48
Implements: blueprint align-nodegroups-tests
Related-bug: #1495593

commit_message:
Add kolla-mesos deliverable repo to Kolla

The kolla-mesos repository was majority voted accepted by the core
reviewer team of Kolla to be adopted into the Kolla governance.
The purpose of this repository is to orchestrate a Kolla deployment
in addition to Ansible but instead with Mesos.  If this experiment
fails, the repository will be filed in the attic.

The core reviewer team has committed to reviewing the changes for
this repository and learning how mesos operates.  Angus Salkeld
of Mirantis has committed 4 full time engineers to work on this
project.

The structure of the governance will be the addition of a team
kolla-mesos-core with only 2 people from Mirantis and the existing
core team from Kolla.  This will improve information transfer and
training of the existing core team for Mesos.  The short term goal
will be to retire this group and move the folks into the main
kolla-core team once they have met our informal requirements for
review output and quality, IRC participation, code generation, etc.

To avoid any code dump, this will be a fresh cookiecutter repository
that Angus will merge with project-config separately.

Change-Id: I902d4c31c13d4941a470553e8013ac7692462f1a

failed in i meant failed creating the resource because...'}, {'account_id': 15881, 'date': '2015-04-19 07:11:36.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 8246, 'date': '2015-04-19 07:35:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1

@Limor, thanks for the explanation. Still rating a -1 for two reasons. If it is believed to be a nova problem, maybe filing a bug in nova is more appropriate, as you already mentioned. Anyway, it sounds like something that will prevent server DNS sovling no matter the request is from Heat or not.

The second reason is about the patch itself. If we really believe Heat should perform a check on physical (server) name length, we can still strive for a single option. As a user myself, digesting so many options is not fun at all.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-19 08:02:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Verified-1

I still think we need to check it from heat as well so we won't get to a situation where we cant create any resource at all because of name length limitation

we didn't add anything new we just exposed to the user
would you like me to ask the community for their opinions?

"Some company have DNS limitations on the length of server name"

This is still not specific enough to actually know what the problem is. What is enforcing this limitation? Is it technical? Company policy?

By default the nova.conf dhcp_domain=novalocal, and this is the source of the 53 char name limit. If nova is configured for something other (longer) than novalocal then this issue would be triggered.

Therefore I'd rather heat.conf had a nova_dhcp_domain option so that installation/configuration scripts can just make heat.conf and nova.conf consistent rather than having to do string math at install time.'}, {'account_id': 15881, 'date': '2015-04-20 06:01:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

@Steve Baker: Ok. SO should I close the bug?'}, {'account_id': 4571, 'date': '2015-04-21 01:27:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

@Limor

If having a heat.conf nova_dhcp_domain option and deriving the nova name size limit from that fixes your issue then feel free to use the existing bug #1239972 and propose that as a change.'}, {'account_id': 15881, 'date': '2015-04-21 07:10:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

Ok i will but this will solve all the servers not all the resources'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-28 13:59:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Verified-1

commit_message:
Add restriction on the physical resource name length

   *Add the restriction to : resource, instance, server and sahara templates

    *The restriction can be set in the heat.conf file

Change-Id: Ie2f8655b0c2dcbd19cc19fbaf4cce56d3e2ade03
Closes-Bug: #1239972

commit_message:
Exclude all BDM checks for cells

Since there are some race conditions with the EBS image checking test,
it's better to remove the entire Tempest class tests just until we
figure out what's wrong with the boot from volume stuff

Change-Id: Ice6a718b6d7b27505696a3c55fc02d44d4b187a7
Related-Bug: #1489581
(cherry picked from commit fa203c3165d4ac61e1c191e6d3c6db54778c3ed7)

To convert to an object, you can just do:

image_meta = objects.ImageMeta.from_dict(image_meta)

in the imagebackend.clone() method.

commit_message:
Fix attibute error when cloning raw images in Ceph

A regression introduced in If03b166d3ecc3e7fa6b7f1a0c69f8ab1cc7b1972
causes a glance image with the type 'raw' in ceph to fail to CoW
clone which prevents launching at all in this case.

The original patch did not update imagebackend.py [1] to use the new
nova.objects.ImageMeta object so the clone() function passes a normal
dict to the is_cloneable() function.

Additionally add another test to ensure that not passing disk_format
will fail, but not result in an exception. It will simply mean that
the function returns that it cannot take advantage of the CoW cloning
ceph provides.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/f2e2a5891d5f5ff9346e6dc8e4dd0e994485245c/nova/virt/libvirt/imagebackend.py#L824

Change-Id: I7ae107bfccab7ff66c09d96856722dd6e60fdd96
Closes-Bug: #1508230

commit_message:
Add method for checking if an iSCSI target exists

This method will be needed by the Cinder Windows iSCSI driver,
simplifying the way of creating an export, making this operation
idempotent.

Change-Id: I5f4e03af90793dd6103d58e06e642964aa0a7559

commit_message:
SAML2 authentication plugins in keystoneauth

Move SAML2 related auth plugins directly to keystoneauth.
Since SAML2 plugins requires ``lxml` which is a heavy dependency,
plugins will be installed on request:

$ pip install keystoneauth[saml2]

Authentication plugins has been renamed to Saml2Password
and ADFSPassword.

Change-Id: I7872f7524902e4b723ab685c684e16162a4af781
Implements: bp saml2-to-ksa

commit_message:
Add --force to grub-install

Grub fails to install the bootloader due to it being on the root
partition of a block device. This is not actually a problem for us, so
we need to force it to succeed.

Change-Id: I335ef04ca8a8a8a5c242d3444b09bcce0a9f51e7

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-12 09:53:40.000000000', 'message': "WIP: region placement policy

This is a WIP policy for multi-region placement. There are several
things left to do:

- Compare this policy to the zone placement policy and decide if we
  should combine these two policies. The reason that we are proposing
  these policies as separate ones is that for some profiles (e.g.
  os.heat.stack), availability zones cannot be set to the object as a
  whole.
- If we decide to have two separate policies, then this patch needs its
  own test cases and tweakings to profiles so that 'region_name' is
  properly passed downstream to the driver layer.

Change-Id: Ia8bde1dd3bbab464e3deae654c41040729264723

commit_message:
Don't use default=None for config options

In the config module default=None is set as the default value,
so it isn't necessary to set it again when doing config options.

Change-Id: I09989ab679d249a9f7dea6af5d53c14dd1726e09
Closes-Bug: #1323975

commit_message:
Magnum: set SERVICE_HOST to eth0's ip address

Magnum k8s functional testing will try to access m-api inside of a VM, the
default setting of SERVICE_HOST is 127.0.0.1 which is not accessable from VM.

This patch uses eth0's ip addr as SERVICE_HOST

Closes-Bug: #1514286
Change-Id: I7f3980896d36a6683e364efa6f78563f10990ecd

commit_message:
Change method to get the user_id

Instead of "find_project", using "find_user" to get the user_id
while the option --user is specified for "openstack volume list"

Change-Id: Iea8472b7b8e709a8792a56575e00003a9cbdaa39
Closes-Bug: #1514145

commit_message:
Fix missing obj_make_compatible() for ImageMetaProps object

This object was never added with an obj_make_compatible() handler for
the many versions we've had since its introduction. This adds that,
rules for the existing versions, and a test for the future.

Note that version 1.6 added values to an enum, so this validates that
an exception is raised during backporting if that field has a value
that would be invalid for the requested version.

Change-Id: I64d40b6fe5e738cf32537c73b9fec57a7fbcdf2d

This method is only used in tests, sometimes even in orphaned code.
This method really just calls the object method FlavorList.get_all()
and wraps the result in a dict.

commit_message:
Remove flavors.get_all_flavors() only used in tests

This method is only used in tests, sometimes even in orphaned code.
This method really just calls the object method FlavorList.get_all()
and wraps the result in a dict.

Lets remove it an replace the few remaining places where it actually
was used with direct calls to the object method.

Change-Id: I990f81af3d24a5b98d1905d44262c138fd2a0283

commit_message:
Document libvirt ping check limitations

This change documents the current limitations of libvirt ping
checks, and how those impact host_alive_status metrics.

Change-Id: Ibf0a8f8ab33843ff9074dad60779bc994648f880

dog command in SheepdogClient Class method instead of
in SheepdogDriver class method directly. Here are two

1.The current implementation can only get volume status
by local sheepdog node, but the SheepdogClient Class also
supports the method to run dog command with remote sheepdog
node.

2.SheepdogClient Class methods are implemented to run dog
command with fine grained Error handling. So it can improve

SheepdogClient Class method.

Closes-Bug: #1512287

commit_message:
SheepdogDriver: Improve get_volume_stats operation

This patch improves get_volume_stats method to invoke
dog command in SheepdogClient Class method instead of
in SheepdogDriver class method directly. Here are two
benefits we can realize as a result:

1.The current implementation can only get volume status
by local sheepdog node, but the SheepdogClient Class also
supports the method to run dog command with remote sheepdog
node.

2.SheepdogClient Class methods are implemented to run dog
command with fine grained Error handling. So it can improve
the robustness and is more readable to run dog command in
SheepdogClient Class method.

Change-Id: I64ca193cd50e6914d0d5fb6cf711c760dfb65b8c
Closes-Bug: #1512287

commit_message:
UI: Task & Execution screen refactored

* code view is now a public template
* emptyform is now a public form

* tasks overview screen
  * add state info field
  * add iso filter to time fields
  * add workflow link
  * refactored detail layout

* tasks main screen
   * main table now has result and
      published columns which use the
      code view template

Screenshots:
http://pasteboard.co/1T2U8Ers.png
http://pasteboard.co/1T2Son9w.png
http://pasteboard.co/1Uj47Rvk.png

Partially implements blueprint: tasks-screen-improvments
Partially implements blueprint: mistral-dashboard-executions-screen

Change-Id: I8978746f645949aed174f893a5195073f156e24d

commit_message:
Add missing unit tests for some PXE drivers

Some of the pxe_* drivers don't have unit tests, while some others have.
Unit tests need to be available for other drivers as well.

Change-Id: I6be2d65c00e575bb0df7309f0e891fdf37cb731f

This patch separates the Ports tests from the Networks tests files
due to file bloat. Similar patches will also split Subnets and Agents
tests to make them more manageable.

I've chosen to keep these patches separate so as to make them more
easily reviewable. There are separate patches to improve the navigation,
tab the Networks details page, and add more content to Port edit/create.

"}]
commit_message:
Separate Ports tests from Networks tests

This patch separates the Ports tests from the Networks tests files
due to file bloat. Similar patches will also split Subnets and Agents
tests to make them more manageable.

I've chosen to keep these patches separate so as to make them more
easily reviewable. There are separate patches to improve the navigation,
tab the Networks details page, and add more content to Port edit/create.

Partial-Bug: 1514048
Change-Id: Ida677f503c22de6d1160f2c972af3f99c04ee389

(3 comments)

Expanding the interface to allow Ironic to inform a DHCP server of the node's MAC addresses is fine - this is addressing a gap in our functionality today. It is within scope because only Ironic knows the MAC address; either Ironic will send this to the DHCP server, or something else will need to poll for it.

However, Ironic does not store the IP address today, and I don't see why it should be responsible for storing that information on behalf of the user. I especially am concerned that this proposal puts Ironic on a slippery slope by shifting responsibility for IP address management into Ironic and out of external network services (eg, Neutron)."}, {'account_id': 1994, 'date': '2014-11-20 06:43:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

I agree with your concerns of Ironic storing IP address. There could be a use case where admins want to designate an IP for a node when using external DHCP providers but I guess this can be addressed after we have a consensus around it. I think we can first go without considering IPs in this BP and have Ironic only help automate white listing the MACs to external DHCP providers.'}, {'account_id': 1994, 'date': '2014-12-16 05:45:08.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 7.'}, {'account_id': 13362, 'date': '2014-12-16 05:57:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Code-Review+1

commit_message:
Make command log in neutron utils.execute() a single line

command execution log from neutron.agent.linux.utils.execute()
consists of multiple lines, and the first line has less information
and it is hard to analyze logs.

Closes-Bug: #1460379
Change-Id: Idca38f26321394596245c9c59b8a9a78c7190423

commit_message:
Swarm: remove explictly pull image

Docker run will automaticly pull image, we don't need to pull it explictly.
Also on master node, we run master, agent service sametime, pull image for
same time will make conflict.

Cloases-Bug: #1501209
Change-Id: If1779cf627c8db242c6470e924f9cb764f12f2d3

Several vendors are still running v1. The current vendors we currently have defined need to have this value set to 1.'}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2015-09-29 20:20:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

David, could you please provide more details why we still need Cinder API v1 by default?

According to [1] we are switching to Cinder API v2 by default for all projects. API v1 will be still available.


[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-September/075689.html'}, {'account_id': 3099, 'date': '2015-09-29 21:46:12.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Because os-client-config isn't only used with openstackclient and the latest version of services. It is also used with the shade library, which provides an API that also hides differences between vendors which are often running older versions of services. OCC is the main tool for describing the difference in these already deployed clouds."}, {'account_id': 3099, 'date': '2015-09-30 08:07:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Ivan, also, to be clear, I'm not saying that you can't set the default to 2. I'm just saying that you must also go through each vendor in the vendors directory and set their default to 1 so that they continue to work as expected."}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2015-09-30 09:13:46.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2015-09-30 09:14:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

David, thanks for the clarification. I'm new to the os_client_config project. All vendors setting was changed with "volume_api_version: 1"'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-09-30 09:18:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-os-client-config-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/39/229039/2/check/gate-os-client-config-pep8/73d1771/ : SUCCESS in 45s
- gate-os-client-config-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/39/229039/2/check/gate-os-client-config-docs/6f72c87//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 55s
- gate-os-client-config-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/39/229039/2/check/gate-os-client-config-python27/016d2cd/ : SUCCESS in 58s
- gate-os-client-config-python34 http://logs.openstack.org/39/229039/2/check/gate-os-client-config-python34/8f5a585/ : SUCCESS in 59s
- gate-os-client-config-pypy http://logs.openstack.org/39/229039/2/check/gate-os-client-config-pypy/7b84673/ : SUCCESS in 1m 41s (non-voting)'}, {'account_id': 2, 'date': '2015-09-30 12:42:19.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-2

I'm going to block this for a second because I'm out of the office today and I'd like to talk to everyone about it.

For context on why I think it's worth having a longer conversation - OCC has grown out of the need to express and workaround all of the ways in which OpenStack makes users' lives a living hell. It's not a place to encode theory wishes or dreams - it's a place to put sensible defaults.

Currently almost no vendors support cinder v2, this means that v2 as a default is a thing that is more likely to cause a user pain. HOWEVER ...

I am in strong support of the v2 push and the follow up patch to set all of the currently known vendors to v1 should mitigate the pain.

SO - let's chat about whether or not this is a thing we want to do here in this library or not.

Let's also talk about the fact that the fact that we have to assert this information in the first place at all is one of the biggest bugs in OpenStack usability and that we should figure out ways that things like OCC don't have to pre-assert versions."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-01 19:00:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

Merge Failed.

This change or one of its cross-repo dependencies was unable to be automatically merged with the current state of its repository. Please rebase the change and upload a new patchset.'}, {'account_id': 2, 'date': '2015-11-09 00:47:35.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

Set volume_api_version=2 by default

Since Cinder has disabled API v1 by default we should
use v2.

Change-Id: I9afd2f58384bab51e394f28a61de5bb44585e5a6
Closes-Bug: #1500938

commit_message:
Change the cluster_address to node_address

node_address is different but not cluster_address
on different database nodes

Change-Id: Ib1fe8b43715248668e800c6bf5dcf18affdce0a4
Closes-Bug: #1493194

commit_message:
Remove test reference to api_versions

API version information comes from occ now. Update the test
to get the version from the correct location. This removes the
last reference to the old api_versions attribute after change
Ifccf7b04168ca45a91a40ace7f33346da893b8d9 merges.

This also makes sure that the version calls actually happen
with the correct 'identity' parameter.

Change-Id: I9b918fa402579fc60319644b1434841fd71ffbcf

commit_message:
Revert "Fix the neutron-lbaas agent config"

This reverts commit 4115c9ae8df72d9138255e4cb33dace318443869. That
commit is a temporary fix for the functional gate. Now, the issue has
been fixed in the neutron-lbaas repo [1]. Therefore, we reverted the
temporary fix here.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/241481

Change-Id: Idd204e094d4a24f4b3440ee3f4294ea9407b467f

commit_message:
Change image to instance in comment

It turns out a delete image is different than a deleted instance in a
fairly fundamental way.

Change-Id: I430d1893875a48ed94428741bd7af2324640e48c

commit_message:
Split version string into a tuple for the user

If the user attempts to pass a string instead of a tuple because that
happens to be how the other clients work, just go ahead and split it
for them to be friendly.

Change-Id: I5593f1c75748e22e44f2693cb8602f8d0f261988
