commit_message:
Add functional tests of auto floating IP

What we ultimately want to make sure of is that hostvars can return and
process the results of creating a server both with and without having
done auto_ip.

commit_message:
Attempt to decode json from the groups metavar

It's possible someone might need to json encode a list into groups, in
order to sanely escape commas. Try decoding the value as json, and if
that doesn't work, fall back to splitting on commas.

Change-Id: I4f94941918854abf2a75f6aa419944d6e7c81a92

Use of contextlib.nested() here is a hangover from the Python 2.6 days. Now we can just use multiple context managers.'}, {'account_id': 9107, 'date': '2015-10-21 09:44:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Samuel Merritt: "Use of contextlib.nested() here is a hangover from the Python 2.6 days. Now we can just use multiple context managers."

Hi,

There are many ways to use multiple mock patchers.

* In Python 2.7 and 3.4 we can write "with m1, m2:".
* We can also use contextlib.ExitStack, it's available on Python 2.7 using contextlib2
* We can use @mock.patch decorator
etc.

My patch is the minimum change to make the code compatible with Python 3. Switching to another solution may require more changes and I would prefer to do that later. It's already complex enough to get reviews on my very simple patches, so I expect that larger patches will require more rebase and more time to get reviewed :-'}, {'account_id': 9107, 'date': '2015-10-21 09:44:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

:-('}, {'account_id': 9107, 'date': '2015-11-08 22:43:44.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

The issue was fixed differently by the change Id472958b007948f05dbd4c7fb8cf3ffab58e2681.'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-19 14:54:37.000000000', 'message': 'Add test.nested() for Python 3 compatibility

contextlib.nested() was removed on Python 3. Reimplement it using
contextlib.ExitStack as test.nested(). On Python 2, test.nested is
just an alias to contextlib.nested.

Change-Id: Icd55d1415fcd3b46720dae564c31f2d5676ddc48
'}]
commit_message:
Add test.nested() for Python 3 compatibility

contextlib.nested() was removed on Python 3. Reimplement it using
contextlib.ExitStack as test.nested(). On Python 2, test.nested is
just an alias to contextlib.nested.

Change-Id: Icd55d1415fcd3b46720dae564c31f2d5676ddc48

commit_message:
Fix UsedLimitsController's authorizer to soft

The rule "limits_extension:used_limits" is used by
"UsedLimitsController" which is a controller extension and it extends
"limits" api. Most of controller extensions authorize user's context
by applying the function "extensions.soft_extension_authorizer()",
but "UsedLimitsController" applies "extensions.extension_authorizer"
and this may cause 403 Forbidden error.

In this patch, I changed UsedLimitsController's authorizer to
"soft_extension_authorizer".

APIImpact

Co-Authored-By: ZhuChunzhan <zhucz@cn.fujitsu.com>

Change-Id: I8a4163ca89236b35c2c6ba10bcd98f8c42ef9089
Closes-Bug: #1497868

commit_message:
Allow int version numbers in the clouds.yaml

OSC blows up if you try to use for example identity_api_version: 2
in the clouds.yaml.  It will only work with a string '2'.  This
fixes that.

Change-Id: I785d37a288126a1582464e907c7f9c9947bac27c

Hi Valeriy,

If I recall at all correctly he said that it influenced the size of the devstack instance that is created to run the functional test against. I've Alex to the review.

One other thing is I notice that you added the same setting to the pre_test_hook for Manila here: https://github.com/openstack/manila/commit/738c7780b75350f48abcd938b79918c86963f92e. Was this added for an unrelated reason?

Chuck,

"VOLUME_BACKING_FILE_SIZE" is used by Cinder LVM driver, that is used in CI. In Manila pre_test_hook.sh it is useful for Generic driver, that uses Cinder. It should not make any gain for other types of drivers, that do not use Cinder as back end.'}, {'account_id': 16212, 'date': '2015-11-08 21:17:32.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-16 19:00:01.000000000', 'message': 'Enable Functional Tests to Run in NetApp CI

To date functional tests haven't been able to run in the NetApp CI
system. It was determined that the OS_AUTH_URL is not set properly
during setup. It was also determined that "neutron" has to be included
in the Jenkins job name in order for the job to succeed.

Also, the value for VOLUME_BACKING_FILE_SIZE had to be increased. This
should be set somewhere other than pre_test_hook.sh though.

Fixes are provided in the post_test_hook.sh and pre_test_hook.sh script
files to make functional tests succeed in NetApp CI.

Change-Id: I7f31d6177c23438d113da3b2e6f77295f414b4ed
Closes-Bug: #1506591
'}]
commit_message:
Enable Functional Tests to Run in NetApp CI

To date functional tests haven't been able to run in the NetApp CI
system. It was determined that the OS_AUTH_URL is not set properly
during setup. It was also determined that "neutron" has to be included
in the Jenkins job name in order for the job to succeed.

Also, the value for VOLUME_BACKING_FILE_SIZE had to be increased. This
should be set somewhere other than pre_test_hook.sh though.

Fixes are provided in the post_test_hook.sh and pre_test_hook.sh script
files to make functional tests succeed in NetApp CI.

Change-Id: I7f31d6177c23438d113da3b2e6f77295f414b4ed
Closes-Bug: #1506591

commit_message:
Get Open Ports for Storm

This patch implements the get_open_ports method to allow storm to be used with
auto_security_groups.

Closes-bug: #1503709

Change-Id: I4939ee9c7d53f760ee654792e017c294a288be0f

commit_message:
Populate mac and ip address of lport

This patch populates the address column in lport table with
mac and ip address allocated to the port. Following is how
the address coulumn will look like

["fa:16:3e:db:fd:5e 10.100.0.5"]
["fa:16:3e:f3:7d:09 172.24.4.22", "fa:16:3e:f3:7d:09 2001:db8::16"]

Change-Id: Ic6dd0b77f017536ad804af88ac59376fec7d6f40

the destination volume will be cleaned up via

commit_message:
Remove the destination volume check in delete_volume

* If the volume migration fails in the middle of the progress,
the destination volume will be cleaned up via
rpcapi.delete_volume. The method delete_volume in manager
should allow us to clean up the database record for the
destination volume.

* The variable update in migrate_volume_completion has been
assigned twice. Remove the second one.

Change-Id: Icb815476943053f1487268b33c28f3575c4fd0dc
Closes-Bug: #1490445
(cherry picked from commit 566a09c322039c27663f71192bb30fca44b7987e)

commit_message:
zuul/layout: fix puppet-integration jobs

* run gate-puppet-openstack-integration-scenario00(1|2) jobs only after
  stable/kilo and make sure they don't vote
* run gate-puppet-openstack-integration-puppet-(lint|syntax) jobs only
  after stable/kilo and make them voting

Change-Id: Ifc2474883c77a22e94fc98e562bb2859f0e28334

I agree with Zhiteng on this, I think rather than converting to lower, we should actually honor case sensitivity.  You'll also need unit tests as Michal pointed out."}, {'account_id': 10674, 'date': '2015-09-19 23:03:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Hello all, you are right. And it seems that this bug happens in mysql/mariadb environment but not heppens in sqlite environment because SELECT search in mysql/mariadb is case-insensitive unless case-sensitive option(such as binary) is specified. So, I will upload new patch to change cinder-volume service generator from case-insensitive to case-sensitive and I will also upload unittests, thanks.'}, {'account_id': 8074, 'date': '2015-09-21 00:04:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Also need unit tests.'}, {'account_id': 10674, 'date': '2015-09-25 06:21:20.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 10674, 'date': '2015-09-25 06:37:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Hello all. I found that checking the existence of cinder-volume was case insensitive
because SELECT search for table having host names of each cinder-volume services was case insensitive.

I solve this bug by adding the check of case-difference with if-condition, not by fixing query for sql,
because it seems that handling for case sensitivity differs from each db services
and option to enable case-sensitivitiy differs from them.

e.g. sqlite is originally case-sensitive and have no such option, mysql has 'binary' option for case-sensitivity."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-09-25 07:39:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

I tried some way referencing the following MySQL doc for case sensitive search, but some way has no compatibility between mysql and sqlite (*1), and other way has no compatibility for python3.4 (*2).

https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/case-sensitivity.html

(*1) filter_by(host = func.binary(host) 
(=> extract 'where host = binary host', this is valid in mysql, but this is invalid in sqlite)

(*2) filter(cast(host, binary) == cast(host, binary))

[{'created': '2015-09-18 06:19:21.000000000', 'message': "Case sensitivity problem in cinder scheduler

Volume creation is failed when we use backend name which consists
of same characters as the name used before but differenct upper/lower case.

e.g.
1. configure 'lvm' as backend name and start cinder
2. reconfigure 'LVM' as backend name and restart cinder

It is caused by the difference of handling for case sensitivity
for backend name.

When checking the existence of cinder-volume/backend
to judge whether new cinder-volume service should be launched or not,
cinder is case insensitive for backend name.

On the other hand, when searching backend in create_volume processing,
cinder(cinder-scheduler) is case sensitive.

That is why I change searching logic of scheduler in create_volume processing
from case sensitive one to case insensitive one.

Change-Id: Ibb1565a183961031495b73e985499455a1ea4c7b
Closes-Bug: #1496694

commit_message:
Case sensitivity problem in cinder scheduler

Volume creation fails when we use backend name which consists of
same characters as the name used before but different upper/lower case.
It happens in MySQL environment.

e.g.
1. configure 'lvm' as backend name and start cinder
2. reconfigure 'LVM' as backend name and restart cinder

It is caused by the difference of handling of case sensitivity
for backend name.

When checking the existence of cinder-volume/backend to judge
whether new cinder-volume service row in the DB should be created
or not, the search-logic is case insensitive for backend name.

On the other hand, when searching backend in create_volume processing,
the search-logic in cinder-scheduler is case sensitive for backend name.

That is why I change the former search-logic
from case insensitive one to case sensitive one.

Closes-Bug: #1496694
Change-Id: Ibb1565a183961031495b73e985499455a1ea4c7b

commit_message:
Remove some old (pre-1.8) Django compatibility code

These lines of code were introduced as Horizon migrated
through several Django versions and are no longer
needed.

Change-Id: I12aae1a843fccc803859da6337a3274339a3741f
Partially-Implements: blueprint drop-dj17

commit_message:
Merge tag '8.0.0'

This is a null-merge of the 8.0.0 release tag back into the master
branch so that the 8.0.0 tag will appear in the git commit history of
the master branch. It contains no actual changes to the master branch,
regardless of how our code review system's UI represents it. Please
ask in #openstack-infra if you have any questions, and otherwise try
to merge this as quickly as possible to avoid later conflicts on the
master branch.

Change-Id: I7fb57bcb6ea824cd62e08ba0d4e728ce0ea773e1

commit_message:
Use Service object instead of DB API directly

In cmd.manage and volume.api we had code accessing DB API directly.
This should be done through Service versioned object instead and this
commit fixes that.

Change-Id: I7c65323279b86c37fce7ffeb2b2626508842edfb
Closes-Bug: 1513806

[{'created': '2015-10-09 16:05:45.000000000', 'message': "Add SensitiveString field type

There are objects that define a String field to hold a serialized json
blob and that blob can have sensitive information in it (tokens,
passwords, etc). When the object is logged, repr will log that sensitive
information. This puts a burden on the code that's doing the logging to
remember to sanitize the object's string form before logging it.

It'd be simpler and cleaner to just have a field type that extends
String so it's the same in all respects except for when it's
stringified. So in SensitiveString's stringify method it just masks the
password on the field value before returning it.

And no SensitiveString does not play an acoustic guitar at your local
coffee shop, he's actually super tough and emotionally walled up, that's
why he doesn't like exposing too much information about himself in the
logs.

Closes-Bug: #1321785

Change-Id: I56466eb8b5d8000ef010f2015f453a9e74dc66b8
"}]
commit_message:
Add SensitiveString field type

There are objects that define a String field to hold a serialized json
blob and that blob can have sensitive information in it (tokens,
passwords, etc). When the object is logged, repr will log that sensitive
information. This puts a burden on the code that's doing the logging to
remember to sanitize the object's string form before logging it.

It'd be simpler and cleaner to just have a field type that extends
String so it's the same in all respects except for when it's
stringified. So in SensitiveString's stringify method it just masks the
password on the field value before returning it.

And no SensitiveString does not play an acoustic guitar at your local
coffee shop, he's actually super tough and emotionally walled up, that's
why he doesn't like exposing too much information about himself in the
logs.

Closes-Bug: #1321785

Change-Id: I56466eb8b5d8000ef010f2015f453a9e74dc66b8

commit_message:
Exclude all BDM checks for cells

Since there are some race conditions with the EBS image checking test,
it's better to remove the entire Tempest class tests just until we
figure out what's wrong with the boot from volume stuff

Change-Id: Ice6a718b6d7b27505696a3c55fc02d44d4b187a7
Related-Bug: #1489581

commit_message:
Using extra-specs in cloned vols for Nimble driver

This patch uses the set extra-specs while cloning a volume. All
existing extra-specs: 'nimble:encryption', 'nimble:perfpol-name'
and 'nimble:multi-initiator' are being reflected in the cloned
volume.

In the existing code, the extra-specs were not being considered
while cloning volumes; the parent volume attributes were used
directly in the cloned volume. This patch uses the extra-spec
values if they are set or if not then uses the default values
for the same.

Change-Id: I7610377e557720038f77ebd318422456e658e2ce
Closes-Bug: #1507821

"My key question is whether we can still support the setting of policy by region or service with these new URL based APIs."  Explicitly, yes. So this was proposed back in Juno, see: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/106558/ and rejected due to:

a) It was felt that if we do this, then we should do this cross-project (or at least have agreement that the other projects would go this way in time)
b) Concerns over multi-process configurations where not all the servers might have the same config (either by accident or on purpose). Several other projects had considered this idea and rejected it because of this reason.

So the question is, are we ready to push this again and have good answers to the above.'}, {'account_id': 5707, 'date': '2015-07-09 08:00:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

henry, thanks for adding the history about this proposal.'}, {'account_id': 6482, 'date': '2015-09-03 05:43:20.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

i'd like to see an API change in the same patch set as well."}, {'account_id': 13997, 'date': '2015-09-03 12:09:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
Remove designate support

It was broken, thus it was impossible that anyone was actually using it.
We do not have a plan for v1/v2 compat support yet, and it's a hard one.
SO - rather than leaving a broken thing in the tree which was not
possible to use, or fixing it and then having a half-baked thing which
people might actually start using, pull it out pending someone stepping
up and caring about it.

Change-Id: I390494fee8c6c7fb5ddde2ce47e7eb598ad5e08b

commit_message:
Image meta: treat legacy vmware adapter type values

Ensure that legacy metadata vmware_adaptertype values are
treated correctly. This value could have been set as "" and there
are existing deployments that use that.

Change-Id: I28e9ca9075f33ff19855408af02bc454780e7c79
Closes-bug: #1506465
(cherry picked from commit 70f4299450a260465102f879758f79160223dc29)

[{'created': '2015-11-06 07:15:45.000000000', 'message': 'Use fake server name instead of id when testing "server_name" param.

"server create" command takes a server name parameter. The server id is
generated by openstack.

When we intended to pass a server name to the unit tests of "server create"
command, we passed server id. It won't be any problem because the fake
server id is also a string, but we should pass a fake server name because
we have a string to fake one.

Change-Id: I9944f0ea2a6c457e4fad8215a54778bca08965ab
'}]
commit_message:
Use fake server name instead of id when testing "server_name" param.

"server create" command takes a server name parameter. The server id is
generated by openstack.

When we intended to pass a server name to the unit tests of "server create"
command, we passed server id. It won't be any problem because the fake
server id is also a string, but we should pass a fake server name because
we have a string to fake one.

Change-Id: I9944f0ea2a6c457e4fad8215a54778bca08965ab

commit_message:
Use oslo_config PortOpt type for port options

The oslo.config>=2.6.0 library provides new PortOpt type to validate
a range of port.

Sample config file has been generated using "tox -egenconfig".

Change-Id: Ie7855af67668054c031dd8a2b081c22d37f52daf

commit_message:
Prevent DBError caused by wrong param passed to get_security_group

Previously, in update_port() we would call _get_port() to get a copy
of the original port before we actually updated it.

This original_port value is in the form of a sqlalchemy object and the method
update_security_group_on_port() uses the original port value to populate
update_port['security_groups'].

In our case, we'd later pass this value to get_security_groups and it would
give us an error of: DBError because we were passing a
neutron.db.securitygroups_db.SecurityGroupPortBinding rather than an id.

Change-Id: Ia311647608781c00448a2f9c1af1c58a41270e2f

commit_message:
Handle VM shutdown case

This patch adds specific handling for local VM shutdown, in
this case OF port is deleted from OVS and reported to all the
applications.
The relevant applications find the appropriate logical port and
delete the relevant flows.
When VM is restarted the flows are re-added as part of the specific
application.

Future enhancment would be to only handle port status updates
in one application (including PACKET_IN) and any other OF protocol
messages and dispatch this to all the registered applications, this
can be done in future patch.

Closes-Bug: #1512713
Closes-Bug: #1513072
Change-Id: If24ed730d3b3808f07c3c187f045d9907e1336c1

commit_message:
Avoid duplicated code in get_tap_devices_count

This change uses get_interfaces_on_bridge instead of duplicating
get_interfaces_on_bridge code in get_tap_devices_count in LinuxBridge L2
agent.

Change-Id: I1ba49e0375b03bf84c74c0d0a79abfcb057b33d1

commit_message:
Port vmware datastore to Python 3

* _filter_datastores(): replace filter() with list comprehension
  to get a list on Python 3.
* tox.ini: add test_vmware_datastore to Python 3.4.

Partial-Implements: blueprint cinder-python3
Change-Id: Ide4e4adf012e155b99b528ddde937df1a48a079b

commit_message:
Revert "Register FWaaS resources to quota engine"

This reverts commit 28948f6559711a0d861fa76f3adf65cda22768fb

Firewall tests in gate-tempest-dsvm-api are failing at a
pretty decent rate since 11/4 and they are over-quota fails,
so I suspect this is the culprit.

Closes-Bug: #1513280

commit_message:
Add specs directory to Kuryr

As the Kuryr community is increasing, a more
structured approach towards blueprints will be
very helpful. So added the specs directoty with
a skeleton and a template.

Change-Id: I8d1ee2c2d76a0d1b82eb5dd5963b33bfb31f5b9d

commit_message:
Few improvements in the quickstart doc

Fixed commands for disabling\stoping libvirt and ntpd in different OS

I encourage to install kolla tools via pip, so user could get rid
of relative paths to config and scripts and run it from everythere.

Change-Id: I77271ce2f72fbaa7d6586a84f7998a9888d9b3a2

commit_message:
Update register_opts hacking check to allow tuples

Update the hacking check for register_opts to allow tuples to be
passed in directly as an argument. Previously tuples were getting
flagged as invalid due to a missing pair of parenthesis in the
hacking check.

Change-Id: Ida2ae47eae4ebc6188696dc25943226acd67b5de
Closes-Bug: 1511010

commit_message:
remove default=None for config options

In the config module default=None is set as the default value,
it isn't necessary to set it again when doing config options.

Change-Id: Id6bbdb3c6b23bcc31d7a02057a73729e89cabb5c
Closes-Bug: #1323975

commit_message:
Return to publish-subscribe for etcd driver

On exception in the etcd client read, we perform a full sync process
this also happen every X time depending on the client read timeout.
This will help recover cases of exception in etcd publish-subscribe
notification and we can also lower the read timeout to achieve backup
sync cycle every X seconds.

Closes-Bug: #1507553

Change-Id: I2d295befa385405e70a1b602fbbfa132bca7c325

commit_message:
Only log router data when created

This patch will supress the constant log writing of router updates.
only on router creation or router interface modification
the controller will log the data.

Change-Id: Ic908a88d321c6cf6ff163cccf81b1c0135ffd7f6
